  {panel}

h3. Summary
The [Pagination|https://docs.atlassian.com/jira-servicedesk/REST/3.1.4/#pagination] used in JIRA Service Desk REST API does not return consistent results

h3. Environment
JIRA Service Desk REST API

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create a GET request for Customer Requests
{code:borderStyle=solid}
<baseURL>/rest/api-name/resource-name?start=0&limit=100
{code}
# Observe the "size" from the result
{code:borderStyle=solid|title=Results}
  "size": 76,
  "start": 0,
  "limit": 100,
  "isLastPage": true,
{code}
# Change the {{start}} to a higher value and re-send the GET request
# {code:borderStyle=solid}
<baseURL>/rest/servicedeskapi/request?start=20&limit=100
{code}
# Observe the "size" from the result
{code:borderStyle=solid|title=Results}
  "size": 36,
  "start": 20,
  "limit": 100,
  "isLastPage": true,
{code}
# Change the {{start}} to a higher value and re-send the GET request
# {code:borderStyle=solid}
<baseURL>/rest/servicedeskapi/request?start=30&limit=100
{code}
# Observe the "size" from the result
{code:borderStyle=solid|title=Results}
  "size": 16,
  "start": 30,
  "limit": 100,
  "isLastPage": true,
{code}


h3. Expected Results
From the above example, Pagination should return 56 and 46 respectively

h3. Actual Results
Returned values are not 56 and 46 respectively
 
h3. Notes
JIRA Service Desk REST API is still an experimental release as per [this comment|https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSD-107?focusedCommentId=853509&page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels%3Acomment-tabpanel#comment-853509]

h3.Workaround
It seems that the Servicedesk api code actually skips “start” parameter amount of entires twice. So, if you add start=10, its actually doing start=20 internally. If you say start=100, its actually doing start=200.
In order to get it working correctly, you would need to use half of the value of the start parameter that you intend to use. For instance, I tried this : 
 {noformat}http://localhost:8080/jira792/rest/servicedeskapi/request?start=0&limit=10{noformat}
and then
{noformat}http://localhost:8080/jira792/rest/servicedeskapi/request?start=5&limit=10{noformat}
